At 2022 New Balance Nationals Indoor, two sets of brothers set out to break the 4 x mile relay record of 17:01.81 by Loudoun Valley in 2019. Newbury Park High School (Calif.) sent out Aaron Sahlman, Leo Young, Lex Young and Colin Sahlman out to chase history.

Description
The 990’s original designers were tasked with creating the single best running shoe on the market. The finished product more than lived up to its billing. When it hit shelves for the first time in 1982 the 990 sported an elegantly understated grey colorway, and a then unheard of three-figure price tag. For avid runners and ahead of the curve tastemakers alike, the 990 was a mark of quality and superior taste. There have been updates to the design since ’82, and more color options, but the 990’s aspirational status symbol aura has never changed. Simply put, the 990 is the shoe so good, that we’ve never stopped making it. The latest generation model, the 990v6 features a streamlined take on the mesh paneling and suede overlay construction, plus FuelCell and ENCAP midsole technologies. The subtle, refined modernization offers an up-to-date pinnacle experience for the 990.

New Balance MADE contains a domestic value of 70% or more. MADE makes up a limited portion of New Balance’s US sales.
Product Details
Features
Suede and mesh upper
FuelCell foam delivers a propulsive feel to help drive you forward
ENCAP midsole cushioning combines lightweight foam with a durable polyurethane rim to deliver all-day support
Designed for an improved fit and comfort
New Balance MADE contains a domestic value of 70% or more. MADE makes up a limited portion of New Balance’s US sales.

5 Reasons To Try The New Balance 990v6!
- History. Introduced in 1982, while the AJ1 released in 1985. in 2022 The new Air Jordan Models are focusing on tech and performance, while the New Balance like pivoted to livestyle primarily. The Air Jordan 37s don't cross over, neither did the 36, 35,34.. you get the point.
- Cut and Sew, Made in the USA. Local is a plus, traditional materials maintains a timeless look and feel, and to the untrained eye, it may look like just a new colorway of New Balance. 
- FuelCell Midsole provides nice modernized twist to the classic model.
- Wide feet versions! Note, usually I get wide, these I really need a regular not wide.
- Availability. You can buy now no hype, in the Grey colorway.

The Fresh Foam X 1080v12 represents a consistent progression of the model’s signature qualities. The smooth transitions of the pinnacle underfoot cushioning experience are fine-tuned with updated midsole mapping, which applies more foam to wider areas of the midsole and increases flexibility at the narrower points. items.Video_Title: How To Clean White Leather Sneakers - New Balance 550
items.Video_Description:
How To Clean White Leather Sneakers - New Balance 550
Welcome back to another episode of Shoe Care Academy with Jonny Bubbles. Today we’re rocking with one of the most popular sneakers of 2021-2022, the New Balance 550. 

Megell didn’t get these all-white New Balance 550’s dirty enough, so Jonny took the liberty and wrecked them even more. 

If you want to see how Jonny dirtied this pair of New Balance 550 sneakers, be sure to follow us on TikTok. 

With our Deep Clean Signature Bundle on deck, we’re ready to give these shoes a proper clean. Stay tuned for some insane before and after comparisons…spoiler alert; our sneaker cleaner did a number on these. 

Jonny started as he always does by removing the shoe laces and inserting the Adjustable Shoe Trees. Then he put two squirts of our Sneaker Cleaning Solution into the water and got to work with the Soft Bristle Brush. 

After the first pass through with the Soft Bristle Brush, most of the surface dirt is gone, but some deeper stains remain. To attack these tough stains, Jonny used the Medium Bristle Brush. Then, he used the Stiff Bristle Brush to clean the outsole.

In order to flush out the mesh portions of these shoes and get them looking bright and white again, we’re going to run them through our sneaker laundry system using our Laundry Bag and Sneaker Laundry Detergent. 

Jonny placed the shoe in the bag along with the laces and a Sneaker Laundry Pod, and put them through a full wash cycle in the washing machine. 

After letting them air dry, all that’s left is to lace them back up. 

See, I told you the before and after was insane. Just look at how good these turned out. Reshoevn8r really has the most complete sneaker cleaning system, with the best sneaker cleaning solution and the ability to throw your shoes in the laundry, nothing else comes close.

items.Video_Title: Conversations Amongst Us | Kawhi Leonard | New Balance
items.Video_Description:
Introducing “Conversations Amongst Us,” creative directed by Joe Freshgoods in collaboration with Black Soles, featuring NBA Champion Kawhi Leonard in the first short film. 

In a culture where you’re only as fresh as your white sneakers and your fit is the perfect conversation starter, communication, both verbal and nonverbal has remained significant in connecting us. Historically and culturally, Black people have communicated with unique words and gestures that don’t have to be explained because amongst us it’s all understood. From the head nod to dapping someone up to African American vernacular, these styles of communication show a collective respect and admiration for one another.

items.Video_Title: รองเท้า 5 คู่ที่สะท้อนความพิเศษของ New Balance ของโอและพีท ผู้สร้างกลุ่ม NBueth | Brand Lover EP.2
items.Video_Description:
ในช่วงไม่กี่ปีที่ผ่านมา New Balance คือหนึ่งในแบรนด์สนีกเกอร์ที่มาแรงที่สุด ไม่ว่าจะมองด้วยแว่นสนีกเกอร์เฮดหรือแว่นคนสนใจเรื่องธุรกิจก็ถือเป็นกรณีศึกษาที่น่าสนใจ ว่าอะไรทำให้แบรนด์รองเท้าดีไซน์เรียบง่าย ไม่ได้ทำการตลาดหวือหวา ก้าวขึ้นมาเป็นแบรนด์ในดวงใจคนรักสนีกเกอร์จำนวนมาก

ในบ้านเราถึงขั้นมีการสร้างชุมชนคนรัก New Balance บนโลกออนไลน์อย่างกลุ่ม New Balance USA, England Thailand Club ที่สามารถต่อยอดจนสามารถจัดอีเวนต์เล็กๆ ของตัวเองได้ ‘Brand Lover’ รายการที่บอกเล่าเรื่องราวของเหล่าคนคลั่งรักแบรนด์ต่างๆ ผ่านเรื่องเล่าที่ซ่อนอยู่ในสิ่งของที่สะสมจึงชวน โอ–ภัทจิยะ แซ่เลี่ยง ผู้ก่อตั้งกลุ่ม เจ้าของอินสตาแกรม @nbl11lus และพีท–นัฏพล หาญตระการพงษ์ Moderator ของกลุ่ม เจ้าของอินสตาแกรม @downtown.bkk มาบอกเล่าถึงสิ่งที่เขาทั้งสองหลงใหล

อะไรคือจุดที่ทำให้ทั้งโอและพีทรวมถึงผู้คนมากมายหลงรัก New Balance ประวัติศาสตร์ของแบรนด์รองเท้าคู่ใจของสตีฟ จอบส์ เป็นยังไง และรองเท้า 5 รุ่นที่สะท้อนความน่าสนใจของแบรนด์มีรุ่นไหนบ้าง มาดูมาฟังกันได้ใน Brand Lover EP.2 นี้

#capitalread #brandlover #NewBalance #NBueth​ #runNBthai​ #NewBalanceThailand​

The FuelCell SuperComp Trainer brings the seconds count performance of energy-return technology from race day to a high milage training shoe. In this execution of new Energy Arc technology, a stacked height midsole houses an arched carbon fiber plate, sandwiched between two layers of FuelCell cushioning, leaving a hollow channel through the middle of the shoe. The plate is flattened into the void with each foot strike, and returns energy as it reshapes, creating a high rebound sense of propulsion. The FuelCell SuperComp Trainer is designed to look, feel, and perform differently.

People love the idea of adventure in the great outdoors, but there’s more to the natural landscape than fresh air and scenic views. Uneven terrain, debris, and moisture are unique challenges to footwear that require specialized construction. For those who take going off the beaten path literally, there’s the Fresh Foam X Hierro, a dedicated, off-road application of our best running technology. The Fresh Foam X Hierro v7 GTX employs a Vibram® Megagrip outsole and a GORE-TEX® waterproof lining to create a protective shell of durability and traction around the signature Fresh Foam X cushioning.
Product Details
Features

items.Video_Title: New Balance Fresh Foam More v4 Review | Un dulce caramelo para los amantes de confort y comodidad
items.Video_Description:
Si quieres conseguir un 5% en la compra de las New Balance Fresh Foam More v4 aplica el código RRR en el siguiente enlace : 
https://top4running.es/p/new-balance-fresh-foam-x-more-v4-mmorlr4?a_box=jybyamb9

https://www.roadrunningreview.com/es/New-Balance-Fresh-Foam-More-v4/REVIEW--101014.html

Parecía imposible que nadie se metiera en la guerra del maximalismo de Hoka pero lo cierto es que New Balance ha logrado meter a sus Fresh Foam More en la mente de muchos corredores que solo piensan en perfiles altos y maximalismo.

La nueva New Balance Fresh Foam More v4 sigue manteniendo, como no podía ser de otra forma, el mismo propósito inicial por el cual se desarrolló este modelo de New Balance.

Redefiniendo sus líneas y mejorando su aspecto estético, esta nueva versión de la More promete conquistar a más de uno solo con observarla por primera vez.

Como aspecto interesante a destacar, tenemos que deciros que la nueva More v4 ha subido un pelín sus perfiles y, de hecho, se convierte desde este preciso instante, en la zapatilla con los perfiles más altos hasta la fecha dentro de la marca estadounidense.

Con el Fresh Foam X entre su mediasuela, hay que reconocer que nosotros, que las pudimos probar en The Running Event (Austin, Tejas), percibimos un tacto mucho más suave y blando en el impacto que el de su previa versión.


TIPO DE CORREDOR:

A pesar de la subida en los perfiles y el cambio en los materiales que conforman el mesh del upper, la nueva More v4 ha permitido rebajarse unos gramos en el total de su peso.

Cada vez convirtiéndose más en una zapatilla súper amortiguada con capacidades óptimas para afrontar entrenamientos suaves pero también algunas subidas de intensidad en momentos puntuales.

La More v4 de la línea Fresh Foam, es una zapatilla perfecta para corredores de peso ligero, peso medio y también por qué no, peso elevado.

Evidentemente el uso que cada uno de ellos le dé a la zapatilla, dependerá de sus prestaciones en carrera.


DISTANCIA:

En este apartado sí que no tenemos ninguna duda. De la More v3 nos enamoraron varios elementos de su configuración y tanto es así, que fue una de las zapatillas finalistas en el marco de las zapatillas de mayor amortiguación.

Su base amplia y la seguridad que transmite es un aspecto a tener en cuenta si lo que buscamos es una zapatilla de este tipo para rodar en larga distancia.

Es evidente que un modelo como es esta NB Fresh Foam More v4 podría servirte para el calentamiento previo a una competición exigente pero también para competir a ritmos más suaves en cualquier carrera de larga distancia. Y por si eso fuera poco, os garantizamos que también os podría servir como zapatilla recuperadora post competición.

items.Video_Title: New Balance FuelCell SC Elite V3 vs Saucony Endorphin Pro 3: We compare two of the years' stand-outs
items.Video_Description:
The New Balance FuelCell SC Elite V3 follows the popular RC Elite V2 as a shoe built for speed on race day. Although it has similarities to its predecessor, the SC Elite V3 sees a number of updates that change both the look and the feel of the shoe.

The Saucony Endorphin Pro 3 receives some significant updates to the brand’s carbon plate race shoe. The biggest of those is the noticeable increase in midsole stack height to 39.5mm in the heel and 31.5mm forefoot, producing an experience similar to super shoe options from Nike and Asics.

In this video, Tom and nick chat through the two shoes and decide which they would go for if it came down to just one.

items.Video_Description:
#newbalance #basketballshoes #sneakers

In this video we go over the New Balance TWO WXY V3:

This shoe released quickly, only 5 months after the successful launch of the TWO WXY V2. Technology featured remains as FuelCell with ABZORB cushioning, and they are very comfortable and responsive on feet. Traction is excellent in the indoor gym, just like the V2 performance. True to size fit, and good stability as well which makes these a fantastic all-around performer, easily one of the best basketball shoes of 2022 from my experience.

Let me know your thoughts on the New Balance Two Wxy V3 in the comments! If you haven’t done so, give the Two Way line a try!

items.Video_Title: Wearing NEW BALANCE 9060 For 30 Days Had SHOCKING RESULTS!
items.Video_Description:
The New Balance 9060 is the latest silhouette to be released by the Boston-based brand. Taking design elements from the 990 series and providing a modernized, futuristic twist, the 9060 has come across as one of the craziest looking shoes of 2022. But there has to be something extraordinary about them outside of their design? Is this actually one of the best sneakers ever made?

Well, I took it upon myself to wear these sneakers for 30 days. I wore them to work. I wore them to the store. I wore them while grocery shopping. I wore them at the airport. I even wore them out on a 10,000 step walk to see just how durable, how comfortable, and how wearable they are.

Since opening their hidden doors in 2006, Boston’s Bodega has evolved, from well-kept secret to global destination, while remaining first and foremost, a local institution. The latest chapter in the Bodega and New Balance collaborative relationship celebrates fifteen years of operation, with a premium take on an all-time icon, the 574 Legacy. A bright primary color scheme that takes inspiration from internationally recognizable iconography like nautical signal flags is applied to a subtly altered 574 silhouette featuring a more prominent, stacked EVA platform and ENCAP system. The Bodega 574 Legacy’s material mix offers a distinctive twist on familiar 574 touchstones. Classic mesh and suede upper construction adds perforations at the collar, lateral ‘N’ branding, and tongue, while the use of grey and reflective accents, and a smoky, translucent take on the original black outsole pay tribute to the timeless 574 design.

items.Video_Title: How To Clean New Balance 327
items.Video_Description:
#SneakerLAB #NewBalance #NewBalance327 

We got our hands on a dirty pair of New Balance 327 sneakers and we thought to document the cleaning process to show you the best way to look after your sneakers. The 327 debuted in 2020 as “the ultimate leisure shoe”. The model is inspired by runners from the 1970s – namely the New Balance 320 (1976), New Balance 355 (1977), and New Balance SuperComp (1977). The silhouette instantly became a hit for New Balance and has since become a go-to-sneaker for most sneakerheads.

Sneaker LAB is excited to announce our partnership with New Balance in the Asia-Pacific regions. Now you can purchase your favourite Sneaker LAB products while you’re shopping for the latest pair of New Balance sneakers. Find out more here.

We used the products found in our Premium Kit and our Leather Care to clean and look after this pair. The Premium Kit consists of our Sneaker Cleaner, Sneaker Protector, Odor Protector and Premium Brush.

Step 1: 

﻿First you will need to prepare your shoes for a deep clean! Remove the laces from the shoes and set them aside as you will clean those at a later stage. Grab our Premium Brush and dry brush off any excess dirt that may be laying on the surface of the shoe.

Step 2:

Spray Sneaker Cleaner around the uppers of the sneakers and focus on the heavily dirtied areas. Then grab our Premium Brush and then dip it into a container of water. Start scrubbing in a circular motion. The water and Sneaker Cleaner solution will react together creating a form that will remove the dirt on the sneakers. 

Step 3:

You will then turn your attention to the soles of the sneakers - you can follow the same process as before but can use more force if necessary to remove any stubborn dirt on the soles of the sneakers. 

Step 4:

Use our Microfiber Towel to dry off the excess moisture and the last remaining dirt. Next, you will set your sneakers aside to dry. 

Step 5:

Whilst your sneakers are drying, you can start cleaning the laces. You will cup the laces in your hand and spray Sneaker Cleaner onto them. Strat rubbing them together in your hands and then dip into a clean container of water. Continue this process until the dirt is visibly removed. Use a Microfiber Towel to ring out the excess moisture and set aside to dry with your sneakers.

Step 6:

When your sneakers and laces are dry, you can do your laces up on the sneakers. 

Step 7:

Next, we will add our protective products. Firstly, use our Odor Protector to remove unwanted odors and prevent bad bacteria from building. If the inner soles are removable, take them out and spray the inside of the sneaker and the inner soles. 

Step 8:

Next, use our Leather Care on the leather sections of this specific 327. If your 327s don't have leather you can skip this step. Leather Care will protect and nourish the leather panels and will prevent cracking.

Step 9:

Lastly, you will apply Sneaker Protector to create an invisible barrier against dirt and stains. This will also make cleaning easier in the future as it will prevent dirt from setting in.

Step 10:

Wear your shoes!

Thank you for watching and let us know what you think of the video in the comments below!

items.Video_Description:

Why is New Balance 574 popular?
Image result for new balance 574
574s were comfortable, could be worn for a light workout, but proved best for more pedestrian situations. For New Balance sneakers, generally speaking, the higher the model number, the more tech. The lower that number is, the more "lifestyle" the shoe leans. With the 574, New Balance broadened its reach.  

Are New Balance 574 good for standing all day?
8. New Balance 574 V2 Varsity Sneaker. These mesh and suede trainers feature a midsole cushioning that delivers all-day support.  

Is New Balance 5740 comfortable?
The 574 has a comfortable upper, but the materials are often mediocre. The cushion is old school and not comfortable over long periods of time. But at an $80 retail price, what can you expect? It is, however, one of the best New Balance shoes of the year as a casual option. 

Best overall. New Balance 574 v2. 
Best classic. New Balance 990 v5. 
Best chunky. New Balance 992. ...
Best retro. New Balance Numeric 440 High. ...
Best new release. New Balance 327. ...
Best value. New Balance 515. ...
Most popular. New Balance 550.  

Is 574 a running shoe?
Image result
The 574 is New Balance's most popular model. The New Balance 574 is the company's archetypal casual sneaker. Initially released in 1988 as a technical running shoe, the 574 has since been reintroduced and rebranded in the early aughts as a lifestyle sneaker 

Description
‘The most New Balance shoe ever’ says it all, right? No, actually. The 574 might be our unlikeliest icon. The 574 was built to be a reliable shoe that could do a lot of different things well rather than as a platform for revolutionary technology, or as a premium materials showcase. This unassuming, unpretentious versatility is exactly what launched the 574 into the ranks of all-time greats. As hybrid road/trail design built on a wider last than the previous generation’s narrow racing silhouettes, the 574 offered a uniquely versatile mix of new, different, uncomplicated, rugged, durable, and comfortable that was adopted as a closet staple across the globe. That’s why today, the 574 is synonymous with the boundary defying New Balance style, and worn by anyone. This edition, the 574 Legacy, updates the classic with an elevated aesthetic.
Product Details
Features
Lightweight EVA foam cushioning in the midsole and heel increases comfort
C-CAP midsole cushioning delivers durable support
Suede and mesh upper
Size & Fit
  380 grams (13.4 oz) 

Counterfeit Products
Counterfeit websites often use the words New Balance in the URL and have content and a layout similar to newbalance.com. If a price seems too good to be true and the product isn't found on one of our official sites, it's probably a fake.

Accept Only Official New Balance Gear
Part of our commitment to helping you get the best performing gear is ensuring the footwear and apparel you purchase is actually made by New Balance.

New Balance does not offer its products for sale through individuals, street vendors, flea markets, or house parties. Only New Balance gear purchased from newbalance.com, joesnewbalanceoutlet.com and our authorized athletic footwear retailers is backed by our 100% Satisfaction Guarantee.

Just because a site has the words "new balance" in the URL doesn't mean it's licensed to sell New Balance products or that the products are authentic. To find a New Balance store near you, use our Find a Store tool. To locate international retailers, click on the flag graphic at the top left of the page to select your country. 

Sole
A thorough study of the sole is very important: comfort, durability, and protection of ligaments and joints under stress depend on the technologies laid down by the manufacturer. On a layer of strong, high-quality rubber, deep tread protrusions are made at the bottom, which prevent sliding on wet and smooth surfaces. Fake makers usually repeat the sole pattern quite accurately, but the official NB logo on the flat part under the heel is extremely rare on replicas. If it is still placed, it is not clear enough and does not accurately convey the outline.
And a small detail near the logo gives a good answer: how to distinguish the original new balance from a fake – the absence of the R trademark registration mark in a small circle.

”Conversations Amongst Us” starring Storm Reid, creative directed by Joe Freshgoods in collaboration with Black Soles. 

To many, it may just be a pit stop in the day, but for Black women it’s a sanctuary. items.Video_Title: New Balance Fresh Foam 1080v12 Review: A solid shoe that struggles to match the competition
items.Video_Description:
The New Balance Fresh Foam 1080v12 needs little introduction. The last two versions of the shoe - the v10 and v11 – have been incredibly popular with runners looking for a jack of all trades, designed for everything from easy miles all the way up to race day.

According to New Balance, it’s the best running shoe they make, which may seem like a bold claim but in this case, it’s focused more on versatility than overall performance.

At its core, the 1080v12 is a cushioned daily shoe that’s designed to be both comfortable but also offer a good level of responsiveness for faster training days. It’s never going to compete with race shoes, but it’s a daily trainer that ticks a lot of boxes.

items.Video_Title: Saucony Endorphin Speed 3 vs New Balance SuperComp Trainer: Which plated training partner is best?
items.Video_Description:
The New Balance FuelCell SuperComp Trainer and Saucony Endorphin Speed 3 are both plated training shoes designed to be used in partnership with a racing shoe, but they approach this brief in very different ways. The SuperComp Trainer has a 47mm stack shoe and is designed to be as bouncy as possible to protect the legs on training runs, whereas the Speed 3 is light and nippy, delivering a fast and efficient ride while also being comfortable on easy runs.

Which should you go for then? In this video Run Testers Tom and Nick discuss the pros and cons of both shoes and deliver their verdict on which is the best.

items.Video_Title: New Balance Fresh Foam More V3 Versus On Cloudmonster: Which max cushioned shoe should you buy?
items.Video_Description:
The On Cloudmonster is a max cushioned shoe that features a thick Helion Superfoam midsole foam for comfort and cushioning. That foam combines with the full-length Speedboard and Cloudtec design to produce rebound and minimise impact over easy day sessions.

The New Balance Fresh Foam More v3 is a shoe that, unsurprisingly, has a lot more cushioning than you’ll find in other road shoes in the New Balance range. That midsole is a thick chunk of the same Fresh Foam you’ll find in other popular options like 1080v11 and 860v12 - a foam that offers a good balance between cushioning and responsiveness.

But which of these two options is worth buying for your next cushioned shoe? Tom compares them both in this video.

items.Video_Title: How To Clean New Balance 550
items.Video_Description:
#SneakerLAB #NewBalance #newbalance550 

We got our hands on a dirty pair of New Balance 550 sneakers and we thought to document the cleaning process to show you the best way to look after your sneakers. The 550 was originally released in 1989 with the 550 following the industry’s trend of brands offering a low-top counterpart to their marquee hoops-ready footwear. This basketball sneaker then received a new lease of life through Aimé Leon Dore’s (ALD) drop of the 550. On September 21st 2020, Teddy Santis, ALD’s founder shifted the trajectory of both New Balance and ALD by unveiling four colorways of the 550 and it has since become a must have for all sneakerheads around the globe.

Sneaker LAB is excited to announce our partnership with New Balance in the Asia-Pacific regions. Now you can purchase your favourite Sneaker LAB products while you’re shopping for the latest pair of New Balance sneakers. Find out more here.

We used the products found in our Premium Kit and our Leather Care to clean and look after this pair. The Premium Kit consists of our Sneaker Cleaner, Sneaker Protector, Odor Protector and Premium Brush.

Step 1: 
﻿First you will need to prepare your shoes for a deep clean! Remove the laces from the shoes and set them aside as you will clean those at a later stage. Grab our Premium Brush and dry brush off any excess dirt that may be laying on the surface of the shoe.

Step 2:
Spray Sneaker Cleaner around the uppers of the sneakers and focus on the heavily dirtied areas. Then grab our Premium Brush and then dip into a container of water. Start scrubbing in a circular motion. The water and Sneaker Cleaner solution will react together creating a form that will remove the dirt on the sneakers. On this particular model of 550, the majority of the sneaker is made up of leather but there are mesh panels that will need more attention when cleaning. Use more Sneaker Cleaner on these areas, and dip the Premium Brush into water and scrub in a circular motion. This process may need repeating to lift out the dirt that has embedded itself into material.

Step 3:
You will then turn your attention to the soles of the sneakers - you can follow the same process as before but can use more force if necessary to remove any stubborn dirt on the soles of the sneakers. 

Step 4:
We then used our Sneaker Wipes to do spot cleans and touch ups on those hard to reach places. The wipes provide a convenient way of scrubbing away dirt on materials like mesh.

Step 5:
Use our Microfiber Towel to dry off the excess moisture and the last remaining dirt. Next, you will set your sneakers aside to dry. 

Step 6:
Whilst your sneakers are drying, you can start cleaning the laces. You will cup the laces in your hand and spray Sneaker Cleaner onto them. Strat rubbing them together in your hands and then dip into a clean container of water. Continue this process until the dirt is visibly removed. Use a Microfiber Towel to ring out the excess moisture and set aside to dry with your sneakers.

Step 7:
When your sneakers and laces are dry, you can do your laces up on the sneakers. 

Step 8:
Next we will add our protective products. Firstly, use our Odor Protector to remove unwanted odors and prevent bad bacteria from building. If the inner soles are removable, take them out and spray the inside of the sneaker and the inner soles. 

Step 9:
Next, use our Leather Care on the leather sections of this specific 550. If your 550s don't have leather you can skip this step. Leather Care will protect and nourish the leather panels and will prevent cracking.

Step 10:

Lastly, you will apply Sneaker Protector to the mesh, tongue and laces of the sneakers to create an invisible barrier against dirt and stains. This will also make cleaning easier in the future as it will prevent dirt from setting in.

Step 11:

Wear your shoes! 

Thank you for watching and let us know what you think of the video in the comments below!

items.Video_Description:
In this video, I go over an honest review on the New Balance 574 in Grey. This has been one of New Balance's most iconic sneakers since it first came out in 1988 and I'm excited to share this review with you all!

The 574 was designed by Steven Smith and he is the known as the "Dad of the dad shoe" for his work across many major sneaker brands. When he first started at New Balance, he designed the following silhouettes:

New Balance 550
New Balance 574
New Balance 576
New Balance 577
New Balance 997
New Balance 1500

...and possibly many more that I haven't covered yet.

items.Video_Title: New Balance SuperComp Range Review: SC Elite V3, Trainer and Pacer tested by two runners
items.Video_Description:
New Balance has made three major additions to its line-up in 2022 with the SuperComp range, which contains the Trainer, Pacer and SC Elite V3. The Trainer is a max-stack plated daily trainer, the Pacer is a short-distance racer, and the SC Elite V3 is New Balance’s top carbon plate racing shoe. 

All three shoe use similar tech like a carbon plate, New Balance’s soft and springy FuelCell foam and the brand’s EnergyArc rocker, but they aren’t equally successful in how they perform for their stated purpose. 

In this video Run Testers Tom and Nick run through the range and discuss whether the shoes work together in a rotation, which is the most impressive for its job, and how they stand up against similar shoes from other brands.

Check out our full multi-tester reviews of the shoe:

items.Video_Title: Are these comfy? New Balance 990 V3 "Grey" Sneaker Review + On Foot Look
items.Video_Description:
In this review, I talk about why the New Balance 990v3 is one of the best sneakers of the last decade both from a quality and a style perspective. The New Balance 990 V3 (M990GY3) initially released back in 2012 and it is still, in my opinion, one of the best sneaker models of the past decade. It's not just me thinking this; many brands have picked up the 990v3 and released their own spin on the model, such as the JJJJound 990v3 duo in Olive and Brown, the Bodega collaboration, the Joe Fresh Goods pair, as well as the pairs in the Teddy Santis pack. And these are only in the past year! 

Some of my personal favorites are the Kith 990v3 “Genesis” as well as the No Vacancy Inn collaboration pair! The grey pair will always be a winner as well; it’s just too clean.

The 990v3 is definitely a mainstay sneaker model even if this "dad" shoe trend goes away, and I don't see this model losing popularity at all. It is definitely worth taking a look at the sneaker yourself and feel the quality + craftsmanship in hand! I'll try my best to show that in this video as well.

https://soundcloud.com/thekobebanks/addiction-ft-dr-malcolm-lex

In terms how I’d rank these, I’d definitely prefer a pair of these over the New Balance 550. NB 550’s are clean (especially the Burgundy Cyan pair and the ALD collab), but the 990 V3 is hands down my pick.

items.Video_Title: New Balance 327 real vs fake. How to spot original New Balance 327 sneakers
items.Video_Description:
#newbalance #newbalance327 #newbalancehombre 

How do I know if my New Balance 327 is real?
Original New Balance shoes have the logo on the outside. On the counterfeits you'll find a mirror image of the letter 'N'. In the original shoes it's in the right place. In most of the versions logo is lined with a material in a different color, usually the same as the other details. 

How do you know if new balances are real?
Image result for new balance 327 spot fake
New Balance retail boxes feature a label on the side detailing style name, size, colour code, and a bar code number. Check that the bar code number matches the number detailed on the tongue labels. The New Balance logo is often found on the insole. 

Are New Balance 327 Made in China?
Where is the New Balance 327 made? Unlike the exclusive 'Made in' models, the NB 327 is made in China 

Why is New Balance 327 so popular?
Image result
New Balance sneakers are a constant reminder of how well archival and modern influences can mesh. The 327 is a great example of this, offering a '70s-inspired silhouette with fresh fabrics and modern spins on the entire aesthetic. Both comfy and stylish, it easily belongs in any summer wardrobe. 

Who made New Balance 327?
designer Charlotte Lee
New Balance designer Charlotte Lee is breaking through those preconceived ideas of how this all works. After working with the brand for only six years, Lee developed the instant-classic future-retro 327, fusing heritage and modern elements to create a new type of heat around New Balance.

Can New Balance 327 be washed?
The suggested cleaning method for New Balance shoes is to use a light bristle brush (old tooth brush) and a light detergent (dish washing or laundry). Scrub the shoes with the brush and use a damp cloth to wipe clean. You can also immerse them in water. Allow shoes to air dry thoroughly for about twenty-four hours. 

What sneakers does Jennifer Aniston wear?
Image result
Aside from being an Aniston-loved sneaker, wearers love the New Balance 327 shoes for their comfortable cushioned support and stylish, vintage nod

items.Video_Title: How To Clean New Balance XC-72
items.Video_Description:
#SneakerLAB #newbalance #Newbalancexc-72

Today we’re working with a dirty pair of the New Balance XC-72. The XC-72 is the epitome of retro-futurism which takes design inspiration from the 70's and gives it a modern twist. The XC-72 first released in 2021 and has become a popular silhouette along with multiple new releases from New Balance.

Today we're cleaning the Moonbeam Black colorway of the New Balance XC-72.

Sneaker LAB is excited to announce our partnership with New Balance in the Asia-Pacific regions. Now you can purchase your favourite Sneaker LAB products while you’re shopping for the latest pair of New Balance sneakers. Find out more here.

We used the products found in our Premium Kit to clean and look after this pair. The Premium Kit consists of our Sneaker Cleaner, Sneaker Protector, Odor Protector and Premium Brush.

Step 1:

Start by removing the laces of your dirty New Balance XC-72 sneakers and grab our Premium Brush dry brush off any excess dirt. This will remove the excess dust and dirt laying on top of the material and will prevent it mixing when the water and cleaning solution is applied. 

Step 2:

Apply Sneaker Cleaner around the uppers of the sneaker. Then you will need to dip your brush into a container of water and drop off the excess liquid. First you will clean the suede panels of the sneaker and concentrate on those sections as you will want to avoid any bleeding of the suede's color. Since it is suede, scrub in one direction and try drying the sections with our Microfiber Towel once cleaned to preserve the suede of the sneaker. 

Then you will make your way to mesh sections of the shoe, you can use more water here if needed. 

Sneaker LAB Sneaker Cleaner New Balance XC-72

Step 3:

Move your way down to the soles and midsoles of the sneakers. Spray Sneaker Cleaner around the dirty areas of the sole and dip your brush in water. Start scrubbing to remove the dirt and use more force where necessary to remove that stubborn dirt that is found on the soles of the sneakers.

Sneaker Cleaner New Balance XC-72

Step 4:

Set the sneakers aside to dry!

Step 5:

You will now turn your attention to the laces of the sneakers. Cup the laces in your hands and spray Sneaker Cleaner around them. Scrub together in the palms of your hands and dip into a clean container of water. Continue this process until your laces look clean. Set aside to dry.

Step 6:

When your sneakers and laces are dry, lace up your sneakers and prepare to use our protective products.

Step 7:

Grab our Odor Protector and spray inside the sneakers. If the inner sole is removable, take it out and spray that as well. The Odor Protector will not only remove the unwanted odor found in your footwear but it will be a preventative method for bad bacteria building up.

Sneaker LAB Odor Protector New Balance XC-72

Step 8:

Use our Sneaker Protector to create an invisible protective layer to prevent dirt and stains from setting in. Our Sneaker Protector will also make any future cleaning easier! Let the Sneaker Protector and Odor protector dry overnight.

Sneaker LAB Sneaker Protector New Balance XC-72

Step 9:

Once everything is dry and your sneakers are looking clean, its time to wear them!

Thank you for watching and let us know what you think of the video in the comments below!

items.Video_Title: New Balance Fresh Foam X 880v12 RUNNING SHOE Review
items.Video_Description:
New Balance says that the Fresh Foam X 880v12 is a shoe that DOES IT ALL! Are they right? The Fresh Foam X 880v12 is a neutral, moderate cushion daily trainer running shoe from New Balance that is designed to help you pack in the miles without getting in your way. The 880 series running shoe is the less-cushioned little sibling of the more-cushioned 1080 series, and it uses the same formulation of Fresh Foam X in the heel and midsole while adding some more responsive foam in the forefoot. It also has extra rubber on the outsole making the 880v12 a super-durable daily trainer running shoe.

I'm still relatively new to New Balance (is that weird to say?), so I'm curious to hear from you about your experience in the 880s or any of the New Balance line of running shoes. Let me know what you think in the comments!

items.Video_Title: New Balance FuelCell Shift TR Review | Good Budget Trainer for HIIT?
items.Video_Description:
READ MY FUELCELL SHIFT TR REVIEW: https://thatfitfriend.com/new-balance-fuelcell-shift-tr-review/

The New Balance FuelCell Shift TR is a training shoe designed for activities like HIIT workouts, classes, light lifting, and short runs.

I went into this training shoe having no expectations, and I have to say, this model has been a subtle surprise. The New Balance FuelCell Shift TR could definitely be a good option to explore if you want a budget-friendly option.

In this New Balance FuelCell Shift TR review, I'll cover a variety of topics to help you decide if this shoe is worth it for your needs.

0:00 Pros
2:10 Cons
4:31 Performance
7:58 Price
8:17 Who are these best for?
9:00 Sizing and Fit
9:33 Weight, Drop, and Insole
9:51 Construction Breakdown
11:45 Final Thoughts

Across the board, I thought the New Balance FuelCell Shift TR did a good job for versatile training and more casual training days.

I like the comfort of the FuelCell midsole and the FitWeave Lite upper is lightweight, secure, and breathable.

My main gripe with this model is the sizing. This shoe's sizing is all over the place, so definitely make sure you do your research on sizing before investing.

If you have additional questions on the New Balance FuelCell Shift TR, drop a comment below or reach out to me personally via Instagram (@jake_boly or @that_fit_friend).
